Ι cannot be persuaded by any arguments that this passage concerning Cainan was in Moses's text, or indeed in any Hebrew copies which the Seventy used3 but that it was certainly added by the interpreters themselves, partly because no reason can be given how it should ever come to be left out of the Hebrew text, and partly because there may be a probable reason given why it should be added in the Greek3 especially when nothing was more usual with them than to add of their own, according to their own will and pleasure.

Huic uni forsan poteram succumbere culpae.
